\title{diststan: Distributed Stan Fitting Across Machines with 'mirai'}
\description{
Run 'cmdstanr' MCMC chains across a small heterogeneous cluster of machines over SSH using 'mirai', gathering every chain's draws into one common directory ready for post-processing. The interface is a drop-in for cmdstanr's sample(): add a 'hosts' vector and let per-machine settings (chains, threads_per_chain, parallel_chains) be scalars or vectors aligned to the hosts. Each machine compiles its own native binary locally and runs one ordinary cmdstanr call; chain ids are distributed as global blocks so the pooled draws combine exactly like a single multi-chain run. A combined live progress board is assembled from each machine's native sampler output.
